text_Pegmatite: Has more distinct colors, smooth stone surfaces embedded in rough, hard looking rock. Has black smooth stone scattered throughout rock. Has large mineral grains.
text_Andesite: More of a neutral, gray tone. Has specks or dots scattered throughout that are mostly white. Has small mineral grains/specks.

text_Peridotite: Has color mineral clustered closely together. Looks rough and phosphorus in texture.
text_Diorite: Has black and white dotted patterns, looking like mold. Looks to have a smoother surface.

text_Gabbro: Has little imperfections in color. More coarse looking.
text_Basalt: More monotoned and muted in color. smoother texture.
